text: Asikkala is a municipality of Finland. It is in the province of Southern Finland and the region of Päijänne Tavastia. The downtown of Asikkala is called Vääksy. It has a canal, Vääksyn kanava. Asikkala has an area of 756.2 km². 192.29 km² of it is water. Asikkala is on the coast of the lake Päijänne. As of 31 May 2013, 8,444 people live in the municipality. == Other websites == * The official Asikkala page Category:Municipalities of Päijät-Häme
